The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal recovery in the presence of perturbations in the sensing matrix. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also proposes algorithms for implementing l1 minimization, which is a popular technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The direction of arrival estimation problem, which is mentioned in the abstract, is a common problem in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SP). Finally, the paper discusses numerical simulations to verify the results, which falls under the category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
